  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-01-07",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to conduct a study of the differences between the depreciation recovery periods used for computing taxable income or loss under the Internal Revenue Code and for computing net income or loss for financial statement purposes. Requires the study to include such recommendations as the Secretary may have for adjusting the recovery periods used for tax purposes to make them closer to the periods used for financial statement purposes."
